    "chartName": "Technological value of patents over time",
    "description": "Description: The graph shows the evolution in the type of patents granted by the EPO and still valid in 2021-Q2 by priority year. There are four types of patents based on the average number of backward citations (BC) and forward citations (FC) to other patents. Adopters (low FC, high BC), enablers (high FC, high BC), pioneers (high FC, low BC) and mavericks (low FC, low BC), where the low is defined as below average, and high as above average. <i>Data Source</i>: <a href=\"https://www.epo.org/searching-for-patents/business/patstat.html\" target=\"_blank\">Patstat - EPO dataset</a>",
